SUMMARY:CPR\, First Aid & HIV Certification
DESCRIPTION:Learn first aid\, infant\, child and adult CPR\, HIV and bloodborne pathogens\, with a focus on injury prevention and safety. Meets L/I WISHA-WAC safety standards. Certificates issued at end of class. \nCan you provide first aid in emergencies\, locate and take care of injuries\, help a choking infant or child and stop cardiac arrest? Learn first aid\, infant\, child and adult CPR\, HIV and bloodborne pathogens\, with a focus on injury prevention and safety. \nModified to meet COVID-19 safety requirements (hands-on only\, no mouth-to mouth). \nMeets L/I WISHA-WAC safety standards. Certificates issued at end of class. \nTaught by Ken Norris\, Retired Firefighter. \nLocation: Upper Blue Building\, Room 7.
URL:https://www.phinneycenter.org/event/cpr-first-aid-hiv-certification-2026-04/
LOCATION:Phinney Center Campus\, 6532 Phinney Ave. N.\, Seattle\, WA\, 98103\, United States
CATEGORIES:Classes,Services
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://media.phinneycenter.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/23135256/thumbnail_IMG_6842.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="PNA Members":MAILTO:membership@phinneycenter.org
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260411T093000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260411T133000
DTSTAMP:20260410T185800
CREATED:20231104T015736Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260116T195104Z
UID:10030422-1775899800-1775914200@www.phinneycenter.org
SUMMARY:PNA Woodshop\, dedicated to Bill Fenimore
DESCRIPTION:Did you know that there is a woodshop in your area? Whether you’re a newcomer to woodworking or an experienced woodworker\, the PNA woodshop is the ideal place to bring your creative projects to life. Whether you’re interested in crafting a bench\, flower bed\, jewelry box\, chair\, or cupboard\, the possibilities are endless. All you need to do is become a PNA member\, attend an orientation\, and complete two safety classes. Once you’ve done that\, you can reserve your shop time and get started on your project.
URL:https://www.phinneycenter.org/event/pna-woodshop-dedicated-to-bill-fenimore/2026-04-11/
LOCATION:Phinney Center Campus: Brick (lower) Building\, 6532 Phinney Ave. N.\, Seattle\, 98103\, United States
CATEGORIES:Services
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://media.phinneycenter.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/05092551/D3A6545.jpg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260411T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260411T220000
DTSTAMP:20260410T185800
CREATED:20260312T202553Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260312T210528Z
UID:10030957-1775935800-1775944800@www.phinneycenter.org
SUMMARY:The Canote Brothers in Concert
DESCRIPTION:Jere and Greg Canote are identical twins from Seattle\, WA who perform as the Canote Brothers. They are known nationally through their touring and teaching at music camps and festivals across the country. The brothers have played an important role in the old-time music scene on the West Coast through a string band class they have been teaching for several decades\, and they are known for their infectious\, positive energy\, and for humorously capitalizing on their relationship as identical twins. \nThey specialize in old time fiddle tunes\, saying “We love the hypnotic ‘in the moment’ experience of playing this American Old Time music.” From the synopsis of the recent documentary about them: “Anyone close enough to be caught up in this vortex of joy\, is likely to end up feeling happier and more optimistic about themselves and the world!” \nDoors open at 7 pm for the 7:30 pm concert in the Phinney Center’s Community Hall (lower Brick Building). \nTickets available online or at prior Seattle Folklore Society concerts\, or at the door (subject to availability).
URL:https://www.phinneycenter.org/event/the-canote-brothers-in-concert/
LOCATION:Phinney Center Campus: Brick (lower) Building\, 6532 Phinney Ave. N.\, Seattle\, 98103\, United States
CATEGORIES:Renter Event
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/webp:https://media.phinneycenter.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/12132512/Canote-Brothers-FDF-2025-800x510-1.webp
ORGANIZER;CN="Seattle Folklore Society Concerts":MAILTO:concerts@seafolklore.org
END:VEVENT
