UID:10029841-1776103200-1776110400@www.phinneycenter.org
SUMMARY:Homebuyer Workshops
DESCRIPTION:Join us to learn the steps to home ownership and the resources that help pave the way! During part one\, we’ll cover the home buying process and best practices using recently sold homes as examples. Plus\, an informative Q&A with a home inspector. During part two\, we’ll dive deeper into available downpayment assistance (DPA) programs. You’re welcome to attend part one or both sessions. \nWe meet at 6pm in the Phinney Center\, Blue Building. Snacks and NA drinks provided. Please RSVP at caitlin.lakere.com.
URL:https://www.phinneycenter.org/event/homebuyer-workshops-2/
LOCATION:Phinney Center Campus: Blue (upper) Building\, 6532 Phinney Ave. N.\, Seattle\, WA\, 98103\, United States
CATEGORIES:Renter Event
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://media.phinneycenter.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/15102626/Homebuyer-Workshops-at-the-Phinney-Center.png
ORGANIZER;CN="Caitlin Spence at Lake":MAILTO:caitlin@lakere.com
END:VEVENT
