SUMMARY:Blood Drive: Bloodworks Northwest
DESCRIPTION:Phinney Center\, Blue Building – Room 6 \nDonate blood to help local transplant patients. \nBlood donors play a critical role in supporting local transplant patients. Over 49\,000 transplants were performed in the U.S. last year. An organ transplant may need up to 40 red cell units\, 30 platelet units\, and 25 plasma units. As a blood donor\, you make organ transplantation possible and provide patients with another renewed chance at a healthy life. Donating blood takes about an hour and is urgently needed. Book an appointment to give blood today and give hope to our community. \nAppointments are available between 10:15 AM to 4:15 PM. Sign up for your appointment by clicking here. \nAppointments are required for the best possible donation experience.\nPhoto ID required.\nFor safety\, we kindly request no visitors under 16 at our donation sites.\nEat a hearty meal and drink plenty of fluids prior to donation.
URL:https://www.phinneycenter.org/event/blood-drive-bloodworks-northwest-5/
LOCATION:Phinney Center Campus: Blue (upper) Building\, 6532 Phinney Ave. N.\, Seattle\, WA\, 98103\, United States
CATEGORIES:Renter Event
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://media.phinneycenter.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/20135530/bloodworks-NW-4.17.jpg
END:VEVENT
